# Mini API — Project Architecture

Read `IDEA.md` before adding features or changing domain boundaries.

## Folder layout

- UI components live under `src/components/<domain>/` (`layout`, `shared`, `request`, `collections`, `environment`, `response`, `history`).
- Pages compose the shell in `src/pages/` (e.g. `Home.jsx`).
- Mock/seed data belongs in `src/data/`.
- Global state (Phase 2+) belongs in `src/context/<Name>/` — not in components.
- Side effects and parsing belong in `src/utils/` (`requestExecutor.js`, `envParser.js`).

## Phase rules

- **Phase 1 (UI):** Presentational components receive props; use local `useState` only for UI (tabs, expand/collapse). No `fetch` in components.
- **Phase 2 (partial):** `CollectionContext` + reducer for collection/request CRUD; `RequestContext` / `HistoryContext` still planned.
- **Collections:** Mutate only via `dispatch` in `src/context/CollectionContext/` — never edit `collections` arrays in components.
- **Phase 3+:** Execute requests only via `src/utils/requestExecutor.js`.

## Imports

- Prefer barrel imports: `from '../components/request'` not deep leaf paths unless same folder.
- Do not put request/collection/history business logic in `App.js`.

## Styling

- Use Tailwind utility classes in components.
- Reuse `KeyValueEditor` from `components/shared` for all key-value UIs.
